 2493  pub fn get_item_val(ccx: @mut CrateContext, id: ast::NodeId) -> ValueRef {
 2494      debug!("get_item_val(id=`%?`)", id);
 2495  
 2496      let val = ccx.item_vals.find_copy(&id);
 2497      match val {
 2498          Some(v) => v,
 2499          None => {
 2500              let mut exprt = false;
 2501              let item = ccx.tcx.items.get_copy(&id);
 2502              let val = match item {
 2503                  ast_map::node_item(i, pth) => {
 2504  
 2505                      let elt = path_pretty_name(i.ident, id as u64);
 2506                      let my_path = vec::append_one((*pth).clone(), elt);
 2507                      let ty = ty::node_id_to_type(ccx.tcx, i.id);
 2508                      let sym = exported_name(ccx, my_path, ty, i.attrs);
 2509  
 2510                      let v = match i.node {
 2511                          ast::item_static(_, _, expr) => {
 2512                              // If this static came from an external crate, then
 2513                              // we need to get the symbol from csearch instead of
 2514                              // using the current crate's name/version
 2515                              // information in the hash of the symbol
 2516                              debug!("making %s", sym);
 2517                              let sym = match ccx.external_srcs.find(&i.id) {
 2518                                  Some(&did) => {
 2519                                      debug!("but found in other crate...");
 2520                                      csearch::get_symbol(ccx.sess.cstore, did)
 2521                                  }
 2522                                  None => sym
 2523                              };
 2524  
 2525                              // We need the translated value here, because for enums the
 2526                              // LLVM type is not fully determined by the Rust type.
 2527                              let (v, inlineable) = consts::const_expr(ccx, expr);
 2528                              ccx.const_values.insert(id, v);
 2529                              let mut inlineable = inlineable;
 2530                              exprt = true;
 2531  
 2532                              unsafe {
 2533                                  let llty = llvm::LLVMTypeOf(v);
 2534                                  let g = do sym.with_c_str |buf| {
 2535                                      llvm::LLVMAddGlobal(ccx.llmod, llty, buf)
 2536                                  };
 2537  
 2538                                  // Apply the `unnamed_addr` attribute if
 2539                                  // requested
 2540                                  if attr::contains_name(i.attrs,
 2541                                                         "address_insignificant"){
 2542                                      lib::llvm::SetUnnamedAddr(g, true);
 2543                                      lib::llvm::SetLinkage(g,
 2544                                          lib::llvm::InternalLinkage);
 2545  
 2546                                      // This is a curious case where we must make
 2547                                      // all of these statics inlineable. If a
 2548                                      // global is tagged as
 2549                                      // address_insignificant, then LLVM won't
 2550                                      // coalesce globals unless they have an
 2551                                      // internal linkage type. This means that
 2552                                      // external crates cannot use this global.
 2553                                      // This is a problem for things like inner
 2554                                      // statics in generic functions, because the
 2555                                      // function will be inlined into another
 2556                                      // crate and then attempt to link to the
 2557                                      // static in the original crate, only to
 2558                                      // find that it's not there. On the other
 2559                                      // side of inlininig, the crates knows to
 2560                                      // not declare this static as
 2561                                      // available_externally (because it isn't)
 2562                                      inlineable = true;
 2563                                  }
 2564  
 2565                                  if !inlineable {
 2566                                      debug!("%s not inlined", sym);
 2567                                      ccx.non_inlineable_statics.insert(id);
 2568                                  }
 2569                                  ccx.item_symbols.insert(i.id, sym);
 2570                                  g
 2571                              }
 2572                          }
 2573  
 2574                          ast::item_fn(_, purity, _, _, _) => {
 2575                              let llfn = if purity != ast::extern_fn {
 2576                                  register_fn(ccx, i.span, sym, i.id, ty)
 2577                              } else {
 2578                                  foreign::register_rust_fn_with_foreign_abi(ccx,
 2579                                                                             i.span,
 2580                                                                             sym,
 2581                                                                             i.id)
 2582                              };
 2583                              set_llvm_fn_attrs(i.attrs, llfn);
 2584                              llfn
 2585                          }
 2586  
 2587                          _ => fail!("get_item_val: weird result in table")
 2588                      };
 2589  
 2590                      match (attr::first_attr_value_str_by_name(i.attrs, "link_section")) {
 2591                          Some(sect) => unsafe {
 2592                              do sect.with_c_str |buf| {
 2593                                  llvm::LLVMSetSection(v, buf);
 2594                              }
 2595                          },
 2596                          None => ()
 2597                      }
 2598  
 2599                      v
 2600                  }
 2601  
 2602                  ast_map::node_trait_method(trait_method, _, pth) => {
 2603                      debug!("get_item_val(): processing a node_trait_method");
 2604                      match *trait_method {
 2605                          ast::required(_) => {
 2606                              ccx.sess.bug("unexpected variant: required trait method in \
 2607                                           get_item_val()");
 2608                          }
 2609                          ast::provided(m) => {
 2610                              exprt = true;
 2611                              register_method(ccx, id, pth, m)
 2612                          }
 2613                      }
 2614                  }
 2615  
 2616                  ast_map::node_method(m, _, pth) => {
 2617                      register_method(ccx, id, pth, m)
 2618                  }
 2619  
 2620                  ast_map::node_foreign_item(ni, abis, _, pth) => {
 2621                      let ty = ty::node_id_to_type(ccx.tcx, ni.id);
 2622                      exprt = true;
 2623  
 2624                      match ni.node {
 2625                          ast::foreign_item_fn(*) => {
 2626                              let path = vec::append((*pth).clone(), [path_name(ni.ident)]);
 2627                              foreign::register_foreign_item_fn(ccx, abis, &path, ni)
 2628                          }
 2629                          ast::foreign_item_static(*) => {
 2630                              let ident = foreign::link_name(ccx, ni);
 2631                              unsafe {
 2632                                  let g = do ident.with_c_str |buf| {
 2633                                      let ty = type_of(ccx, ty);
 2634                                      llvm::LLVMAddGlobal(ccx.llmod, ty.to_ref(), buf)
 2635                                  };
 2636                                  if attr::contains_name(ni.attrs, "weak_linkage") {
 2637                                      lib::llvm::SetLinkage(g, lib::llvm::ExternalWeakLinkage);
 2638                                  }
 2639                                  g
 2640                              }
 2641                          }
 2642                      }
 2643                  }
 2644  
 2645                  ast_map::node_variant(ref v, enm, pth) => {
 2646                      let llfn;
 2647                      match v.node.kind {
 2648                          ast::tuple_variant_kind(ref args) => {
 2649                              assert!(args.len() != 0u);
 2650                              let pth = vec::append((*pth).clone(),
 2651                                                    [path_name(enm.ident),
 2652                                                     path_name((*v).node.name)]);
 2653                              let ty = ty::node_id_to_type(ccx.tcx, id);
 2654                              let sym = exported_name(ccx, pth, ty, enm.attrs);
 2655  
 2656                              llfn = match enm.node {
 2657                                  ast::item_enum(_, _) => {
 2658                                      register_fn(ccx, (*v).span, sym, id, ty)
 2659                                  }
 2660                                  _ => fail!("node_variant, shouldn't happen")
 2661                              };
 2662                          }
 2663                          ast::struct_variant_kind(_) => {
 2664                              fail!("struct variant kind unexpected in get_item_val")
 2665                          }
 2666                      }
 2667                      set_inline_hint(llfn);
 2668                      llfn
 2669                  }
 2670  
 2671                  ast_map::node_struct_ctor(struct_def, struct_item, struct_path) => {
 2672                      // Only register the constructor if this is a tuple-like struct.
 2673                      match struct_def.ctor_id {
 2674                          None => {
 2675                              ccx.tcx.sess.bug("attempt to register a constructor of \
 2676                                                a non-tuple-like struct")
 2677                          }
 2678                          Some(ctor_id) => {
 2679                              let ty = ty::node_id_to_type(ccx.tcx, ctor_id);
 2680                              let sym = exported_name(ccx, (*struct_path).clone(), ty,
 2681                                                      struct_item.attrs);
 2682                              let llfn = register_fn(ccx, struct_item.span,
 2683                                                     sym, ctor_id, ty);
 2684                              set_inline_hint(llfn);
 2685                              llfn
 2686                          }
 2687                      }
 2688                  }
 2689  
 2690                  ref variant => {
 2691                      ccx.sess.bug(fmt!("get_item_val(): unexpected variant: %?",
 2692                                   variant))
 2693                  }
 2694              };
 2695  
 2696              if !exprt && !ccx.reachable.contains(&id) {
 2697                  lib::llvm::SetLinkage(val, lib::llvm::InternalLinkage);
 2698              }
 2699  
 2700              ccx.item_vals.insert(id, val);
 2701              val
 2702          }
 2703      }
 2704  }

 2706  pub fn register_method(ccx: @mut CrateContext,
 2707                         id: ast::NodeId,
 2708                         path: @ast_map::path,
 2709                         m: @ast::method) -> ValueRef {
 2710      let mty = ty::node_id_to_type(ccx.tcx, id);
 2711  
 2712      let mut path = (*path).clone();
 2713      path.push(path_pretty_name(m.ident, token::gensym("meth") as u64));
 2714  
 2715      let sym = exported_name(ccx, path, mty, m.attrs);
 2716  
 2717      let llfn = register_fn(ccx, m.span, sym, id, mty);
 2718      set_llvm_fn_attrs(m.attrs, llfn);
 2719      llfn
 2720  }

 2902  pub fn create_module_map(ccx: &mut CrateContext) -> ValueRef {
 2903      let elttype = Type::struct_([ccx.int_type, ccx.int_type], false);
 2904      let maptype = Type::array(&elttype, (ccx.module_data.len() + 1) as u64);
 2905      let map = do "_rust_mod_map".with_c_str |buf| {
 2906          unsafe {
 2907              llvm::LLVMAddGlobal(ccx.llmod, maptype.to_ref(), buf)
 2908          }
 2909      };
 2910      lib::llvm::SetLinkage(map, lib::llvm::InternalLinkage);
 2911      let mut elts: ~[ValueRef] = ~[];
 2912  
 2913      // This is not ideal, but the borrow checker doesn't
 2914      // like the multiple borrows. At least, it doesn't
 2915      // like them on the current snapshot. (2013-06-14)
 2916      let mut keys = ~[];
 2917      for (k, _) in ccx.module_data.iter() {
 2918          keys.push(k.to_managed());
 2919      }
 2920  
 2921      for key in keys.iter() {
 2922          let val = *ccx.module_data.find_equiv(key).unwrap();
 2923          let s_const = C_cstr(ccx, *key);
 2924          let s_ptr = p2i(ccx, s_const);
 2925          let v_ptr = p2i(ccx, val);
 2926          let elt = C_struct([s_ptr, v_ptr]);
 2927          elts.push(elt);
 2928      }
 2929      let term = C_struct([C_int(ccx, 0), C_int(ccx, 0)]);
 2930      elts.push(term);
 2931      unsafe {
 2932          llvm::LLVMSetInitializer(map, C_array(elttype, elts));
 2933      }
 2934      return map;
 2935  }

 2938  pub fn decl_crate_map(sess: session::Session, mapmeta: LinkMeta,
 2939                        llmod: ModuleRef) -> ValueRef {
 2940      let targ_cfg = sess.targ_cfg;
 2941      let int_type = Type::int(targ_cfg.arch);
 2942      let mut n_subcrates = 1;
 2943      let cstore = sess.cstore;
 2944      while cstore::have_crate_data(cstore, n_subcrates) { n_subcrates += 1; }
 2945      let mapname = if *sess.building_library {
 2946          fmt!("%s_%s_%s", mapmeta.name, mapmeta.vers, mapmeta.extras_hash)
 2947      } else {
 2948          ~"toplevel"
 2949      };
 2950      let sym_name = ~"_rust_crate_map_" + mapname;
 2951      let arrtype = Type::array(&int_type, n_subcrates as u64);
 2952      let maptype = Type::struct_([Type::i32(), Type::i8p(), int_type, arrtype], false);
 2953      let map = do sym_name.with_c_str |buf| {
 2954          unsafe {
 2955              llvm::LLVMAddGlobal(llmod, maptype.to_ref(), buf)
 2956          }
 2957      };
 2958      // On windows we'd like to export the toplevel cratemap
 2959      // such that we can find it from libstd.
 2960      if targ_cfg.os == session::OsWin32 && "toplevel" == mapname {
 2961          lib::llvm::SetLinkage(map, lib::llvm::DLLExportLinkage);
 2962      } else {
 2963          lib::llvm::SetLinkage(map, lib::llvm::ExternalLinkage);
 2964      }
 2965  
 2966      return map;
 2967  }

 2969  pub fn fill_crate_map(ccx: @mut CrateContext, map: ValueRef) {
 2970      let mut subcrates: ~[ValueRef] = ~[];
 2971      let mut i = 1;
 2972      let cstore = ccx.sess.cstore;
 2973      while cstore::have_crate_data(cstore, i) {
 2974          let cdata = cstore::get_crate_data(cstore, i);
 2975          let nm = fmt!("_rust_crate_map_%s_%s_%s",
 2976                        cdata.name,
 2977                        cstore::get_crate_vers(cstore, i),
 2978                        cstore::get_crate_hash(cstore, i));
 2979          let cr = do nm.with_c_str |buf| {
 2980              unsafe {
 2981                  llvm::LLVMAddGlobal(ccx.llmod, ccx.int_type.to_ref(), buf)
 2982              }
 2983          };
 2984          subcrates.push(p2i(ccx, cr));
 2985          i += 1;
 2986      }
 2987      subcrates.push(C_int(ccx, 0));
 2988  
 2989      unsafe {
 2990          let mod_map = create_module_map(ccx);
 2991          llvm::LLVMSetInitializer(map, C_struct(
 2992              [C_i32(1),
 2993               // FIXME #8431 This used to be the annihilate function, now it's nothing
 2994               C_null(Type::i8p()),
 2995               p2i(ccx, mod_map),
 2996               C_array(ccx.int_type, subcrates)]));
 2997      }
 2998  }

 3021  pub fn write_metadata(cx: &mut CrateContext, crate: &ast::Crate) {
 3022      if !*cx.sess.building_library { return; }
 3023  
 3024      let encode_inlined_item: encoder::encode_inlined_item =
 3025          |ecx, ebml_w, path, ii|
 3026          astencode::encode_inlined_item(ecx, ebml_w, path, ii, cx.maps);
 3027  
 3028      let encode_parms = crate_ctxt_to_encode_parms(cx, encode_inlined_item);
 3029      let llmeta = C_bytes(encoder::encode_metadata(encode_parms, crate));
 3030      let llconst = C_struct([llmeta]);
 3031      let mut llglobal = do "rust_metadata".with_c_str |buf| {
 3032          unsafe {

 3034          }
 3035      };
 3036      unsafe {
 3037          llvm::LLVMSetInitializer(llglobal, llconst);
 3038          do cx.sess.targ_cfg.target_strs.meta_sect_name.with_c_str |buf| {
 3039              llvm::LLVMSetSection(llglobal, buf)
 3040          };
 3041          lib::llvm::SetLinkage(llglobal, lib::llvm::InternalLinkage);
 3042  
 3043          let t_ptr_i8 = Type::i8p();
 3044          llglobal = llvm::LLVMConstBitCast(llglobal, t_ptr_i8.to_ref());
 3045          let llvm_used = do "llvm.used".with_c_str |buf| {
 3046              llvm::LLVMAddGlobal(cx.llmod, Type::array(&t_ptr_i8, 1).to_ref(), buf)
 3047          };
 3048          lib::llvm::SetLinkage(llvm_used, lib::llvm::AppendingLinkage);
 3049          llvm::LLVMSetInitializer(llvm_used, C_array(t_ptr_i8, [llglobal]));
 3050      }
 3051  }

 3078  pub fn trans_crate(sess: session::Session,
 3079                     crate: &ast::Crate,
 3080                     analysis: &CrateAnalysis,
 3081                     output: &Path) -> CrateTranslation {
 3082      // Before we touch LLVM, make sure that multithreading is enabled.
 3083      if unsafe { !llvm::LLVMRustStartMultithreading() } {
 3084          //sess.bug("couldn't enable multi-threaded LLVM");
 3085      }
 3086  
 3087      let mut symbol_hasher = hash::default_state();
 3088      let link_meta = link::build_link_meta(sess, crate, output, &mut symbol_hasher);
 3089  
 3090      // Append ".rc" to crate name as LLVM module identifier.
 3091      //
 3092      // LLVM code generator emits a ".file filename" directive
 3093      // for ELF backends. Value of the "filename" is set as the
 3094      // LLVM module identifier.  Due to a LLVM MC bug[1], LLVM
 3095      // crashes if the module identifer is same as other symbols
 3096      // such as a function name in the module.
 3097      // 1. http://llvm.org/bugs/show_bug.cgi?id=11479
 3098      let llmod_id = link_meta.name.to_owned() + ".rc";
 3099  
 3100      let ccx = @mut CrateContext::new(sess,
 3101                                       llmod_id,
 3102                                       analysis.ty_cx,
 3103                                       analysis.exp_map2,
 3104                                       analysis.maps,
 3105                                       symbol_hasher,
 3106                                       link_meta,
 3107                                       analysis.reachable);
 3108  
 3109      if ccx.sess.opts.debuginfo {
 3110          debuginfo::initialize(ccx, crate);
 3111      }
 3112  
 3113      {
 3114          let _icx = push_ctxt("text");
 3115          trans_mod(ccx, &crate.module);
 3116      }
 3117  
 3118      decl_gc_metadata(ccx, llmod_id);
 3119      fill_crate_map(ccx, ccx.crate_map);
 3120  
 3121      // NOTE win32: wart with exporting crate_map symbol
 3122      // We set the crate map (_rust_crate_map_toplevel) to use dll_export
 3123      // linkage but that ends up causing the linker to look for a
 3124      // __rust_crate_map_toplevel symbol (extra underscore) which it will
 3125      // subsequently fail to find. So to mitigate that we just introduce
 3126      // an alias from the symbol it expects to the one that actually exists.
 3127      if ccx.sess.targ_cfg.os == session::OsWin32 &&
 3128         !*ccx.sess.building_library {
 3129  
 3130          let maptype = val_ty(ccx.crate_map).to_ref();
 3131  
 3132          do "__rust_crate_map_toplevel".with_c_str |buf| {
 3133              unsafe {
 3134                  llvm::LLVMAddAlias(ccx.llmod, maptype,
 3135                                     ccx.crate_map, buf);
 3136              }
 3137          }
 3138      }
 3139  
 3140      glue::emit_tydescs(ccx);
 3141      write_abi_version(ccx);
 3142      if ccx.sess.opts.debuginfo {
 3143          debuginfo::finalize(ccx);
 3144      }
 3145  
 3146      // Translate the metadata.
 3147      write_metadata(ccx, crate);
 3148      if ccx.sess.trans_stats() {
 3149          io::println("--- trans stats ---");
 3150          printfln!("n_static_tydescs: %u", ccx.stats.n_static_tydescs);
 3151          printfln!("n_glues_created: %u", ccx.stats.n_glues_created);
 3152          printfln!("n_null_glues: %u", ccx.stats.n_null_glues);
 3153          printfln!("n_real_glues: %u", ccx.stats.n_real_glues);
 3154  
 3155          printfln!("n_fns: %u", ccx.stats.n_fns);
 3156          printfln!("n_monos: %u", ccx.stats.n_monos);
 3157          printfln!("n_inlines: %u", ccx.stats.n_inlines);
 3158          printfln!("n_closures: %u", ccx.stats.n_closures);
 3159          io::println("fn stats:");
 3160          do sort::quick_sort(ccx.stats.fn_stats) |&(_, _, insns_a), &(_, _, insns_b)| {
 3161              insns_a > insns_b
 3162          }
 3163          for tuple in ccx.stats.fn_stats.iter() {
 3164              match *tuple {
 3165                  (ref name, ms, insns) => {
 3166                      printfln!("%u insns, %u ms, %s", insns, ms, *name);
 3167                  }
 3168              }
 3169          }
 3170      }
 3171      if ccx.sess.count_llvm_insns() {
 3172          for (k, v) in ccx.stats.llvm_insns.iter() {
